We're just gonna toss those in so
they're all just

00:01:48.210 --> 00:01:52.090
going in the bowl and then we're gonna give them a good stir.

00:01:52.090 --> 00:01:56.560
At this point you wanna let them sit at
room temperature and marinate for only

00:01:56.560 --> 00:01:59.560
about 30 minutes, but you certainly could
go a little bit longer.

00:01:59.560 --> 00:02:04.050
You can serve the tomatoes atop a bed a
greens for a gorgeous summer salad.

00:02:04.050 --> 00:02:10.069
Or spoon them atop crusty grilled
bread for a terrific summer appetizer.

00:02:10.069 --> 00:02:14.579
You can easily grow your own Bonnie
cherry tomatoes to prepare this recipe.

00:02:14.579 --> 00:02:16.769
Plant your tomato in a raised bed

00:02:16.769 --> 00:02:19.769
are large container filled with good
quality potting soil and

00:02:19.769 --> 00:02:23.890
where it gets good sun. To plant, remove
the label and gently tear away the bottom of the pot.

00:02:23.890 --> 00:02:28.450
You can cut off the lower leaves just to
make it easier to handle the plant.

00:02:28.450 --> 00:02:31.609
The plant will grow fine with or without
cutting off the leaves.

00:02:31.609 --> 00:02:35.150
Plant the tomato so that two-thirds of the
plant is buried.

00:02:35.150 --> 00:02:38.230
The buried stem sprouts roots to make
the plant stronger.

